Text.Value: Did you now? About time she showed her... erm, does she have a face?

EditorData.NodeContext: Almost to herself, she really doesn't know

Text.Value: I'll be sure to let your mother know you'll be home before she knows it - for a nice long visit.
She still wants to know when she'll see you again, sir. I avoid giving any answers. But she misses you.
Days rather than tendays.
Perhaps.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: Mystra is a god. She can handle this without taking your life in the bargain, surely!

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara aghast. Gale told her about Mystra' plan

Text.Value: To be honest, it's been nothing but one escalating problem after the other.
I think so, yes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: I need a moment. There's much to consider.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: There's a glint in your eye, Mr Dekarios. Explain.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Can only be triggered after she has returned after her pigeon-hunting.

Text.Value: She really wants to kill you, Gale? To squander your life? Is that really a god you want to serve?
I don't know, Tara, I'm feeling a little... tentacular.
I can't fathom why you're speaking in the past tense, sir. If you've lost the damn thing, I expect you to get busy finding it. It could be the key to your salvation.
Let's just say, I'm glad it's over with.
She told me the orb is actually the Karsite Weave. I think there's a chance I could control it, if I reforge the Crown.
Go! I don't want to look at you anymore! Go on!

EditorData.NodeContext: Feigning anger but actually she's heartbroken because Gale has said he's going to explode himself if needed.

Text.Value: What's that? For a moment I thought my friend Mr Dekarios was near, but now I see it's only the ghost of one of Mystra's playthings.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara is angry at Gale, masking her hurt that he might die.

Text.Value: Like winning my unwavering affection, for instance. And oh, you did a very good job of that.
I have. The ghost of love past.
Start at the top, then.
It isn't your job to do the gods' dirty work for them. If Mystra wants to intervene, let her do so at her own peril.
I'm still considering all my options.
Well. I won't lie, this is a terrible problem. But do you know who's a dab hand at solving terrible problems? Brilliant wizards.
Elminster? And what did he have to say for himself?
Hmm. I smell the outer planes on you. Mystra, then, is it?
You are too precious to meet your end splattered all over an illithid monstrosity. No no. I won't allow it.
My gods! She didn't. She wouldn't!

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara aghast. Gale told her about Mystra' plan

Text.Value: That's not the look you have when you've been on a spending spree, Mr Dekarios. You look... guilty.
I hope he apologised for that horrid message he brought the last time he graced us with his presence.

EditorData.NodeContext: sarcasm

Text.Value: I won't ask for more details. All I know is we can lick this thing. Rough-tongued and ready.
Goodbye, Mr Dekarios. Try to regrow the bits of your brain that parasite has obviously been eating. Before it's too late.
Good point - I'll have another visit.
Mr Dekarios. Gale. You are the finest mind - the finest wizard - I have ever had the pleasure to know.
You don't want to know.
Farewell, sir.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: Don't be too hard on yourself, sir. You've been like that all your life.
I'm not sure...
What is it, Mr Dekarios?
All right, Mr Dekarios?
Well, if it isn't my favourite fellow himself.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Greeting in the camp, before meeting Elminster.

Text.Value: Well! We are in Baldur's Gate, aren't we? You've always been very positive about the selection of books in Sorcerous Sundries. An opportunity for research, perhaps.
Leave.
Oh? Well, do go on, Mr Dekarios.

EditorData.NodeContext: Realizes something is amiss. Starts to get a little worried.

Text.Value: Unfortunately.
Must be the beard.
I thought you'd have learned by now what pursuing such power can cost. If you haven't... well, I'm not sure who's left to teach it to you.
Elminster also brought instructions from Mystra. I'm to detonate the orb once I find the 'Heart of the Absolute.'
When this is all over I'll be waiting for you, with a crackling fire and good book at the ready. Good luck, darling.
If I have to go search for it myself, I'm going to take it out on the legs of your leather chaise.
And - Mr Dekarios - please. The beard. I'd cut it down myself if I could hold a razor.
This disobedience of yours had best continue once you find this Heart of the Absolute, Gale. That's all I have to say to you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara is angry at Gale, masking her hurt that he might die.

Text.Value: Ah! Oh, goodness. That thing on your face is even worse than I remember.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Greeting in the camp, before meeting Elminster.
EditorData.NodeContext: A shout of surprise. Talking about Gale's beard, which she detests

Text.Value: You've a Netherese orb in your belly, a tadpole in your head, and you've been sleeping in what amounts to a very well-appointed ditch. So go on - explain yourself.
Oh. That's no fun. I was hoping for a good bit of gossip.
No. I'm determined to find another way.
I suppose I'll leave it be, so long as this thing you're 'handling' won't blow us all to smithereens.
No more guilt trips, Tara. Please.
Mr Dekarios, if you have to ask, there's no hope for you at all.
Don't be silly. What is it really?

EditorData.NodeContext: Poo-pooing what he said.

Text.Value: I faced the Chosen of Myrkul and got a glimpse of where this journey will lead us.
We'll talk later, hmm?

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: That you wouldn't figure a way out of it. My clever friend never leaves a knot knotted. This parasite is one more knot, so get to tugging threads.
I've mostly been looking for artefacts to help stabilise me. It's a full-time job.
Back in Moonrise Towers I saw an elder brain, wearing a curious Netherese crown. I need to find out more about it...
I've been a bit preoccupied, you know.
If you must know, there is someone...
Well, sir? How goes the search?
I'm not one to pry. I'd rather make up all the juicy details myself over tea with your mother.
Damn the Absolute. Damn Mystra. Damn it all, if you go through with this, Gale.
Not in the slightest.
Indeed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: You are my pet. And I'm yours. A perfect circle of companionship. I don't know about you, but I wouldn't have it any other way.
That parasite in your head seems to be quiet enough, thank the gods.
I know that look. Come on - out with it. What's happened?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale spoke to Elminster 2 in LOW and received the instruction to come speak with Mystra

Text.Value: I know that, but she doesn't. She'd keel over if she knew just how you'd tried to manipulate the Weave.
But you're wise - and wiser all the time. Do what Mystra asks, and I'm positive she will cure you of that wretched orb.
Mr Dekarios. Gale. No.

EditorData.NodeContext: Forcefully.

Text.Value: Ah. Mr Dekarios. You seem... different. Better. What's the meaning of this?
Hello, sir.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Greeting node from end of act 2 onwards, if there's nothing else to discuss.
EditorData.NodeContext: Very warm and affectionate.

Text.Value: We had our hands on a book written by Karsus himself. It might've been able to help me.
When you tried to control the Weave - when it all went, pardon my language, belly up - I was terrified.
Leave.
So? What led to this decision?
Tell me you aren't going to go through with it!

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara aghast. Gale told her about Mystra' plan

Text.Value: I'm glad you aren't considering such a ridiculous proposition. You've a good head on your shoulders, Mr Dekarios. No matter what anyone says.
I've got hold of a book written by Karsus himself. It might be able to help me.
There's a book I need to get from Sorcerous Sundries. To understand the crown I saw atop the elder brain.
There's not much escapes her sights, that's for certain. But she can hardly have told you this herself. Why so sure?
I don't care if she does. She's not my goddess any longer.
That's quite all right, sir. Quiet company is more my specialty, anyway.
But if you've still a warm lap on you when all's said and done, we can still be friends. I suppose.
Walk away.
You should return to Waterdeep now, Tara. It isn't safe here.
I defied Mystra's orders. She's lost to me forever.
Can we talk?

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: There's a fireplace and a half-read book waiting for us in Waterdeep. It's about time we went home.
I promise I'll try.
So - what's your plan? Why this region? What in particular are you looking for?
Very tough.

EditorData.NodeContext: Making fun of Gale.

Text.Value: You've got a chance at salvation in front of you. Don't be a fool. Take it.
No such luck. He came to summon me on Mystra's behalf. Though I'm not sure it's a summons I want to obey.
I've been summoned by Mystra. She's willing to speak to me.
I assure you I do.
If she has, she could have offered it long before now.
I'm going to need more details, sir.
Well, out with it then. How did it go?
Now go on. We don't want to make a scene, do we? There's a good lad.

EditorData.NodeContext: Avoiding crying, shutting down the convo before it goes too far.

Text.Value: I didn't stay long enough to find out.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: If Gale didn't make it far enough in the conversation to learn the quest - e.g. died due to status effect

Text.Value: I've no need of your approval, Tara. I don't need a cat that badly.
If you're that immature, you're not ready for one tenth of Karsus' powers. And I'll play no part in helping you get them.
I'd rather not talk about it.
Do I need a reason to be looking well, Tara?
Absolutely incredible. I can hardly believe it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: Hear what she has to say. At the very least you'll be better armed to survive what comes next. And that's the most important thing.
If that's all, then what comes after is for you to decide, Mr Dekarios. Think well on all that's happened, and stay true to that heart of yours. It's a good one.
Why did she summon you? And how worried do I need to be about what she's asked of you this time?
Unless you've got Mr Dek- erm, Gale in your pocket, I don't believe we have terribly much to say to one another.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stumbling because she doesn't usually call him by his first name.

Text.Value: I'm your only old friend, Mr Dekarios. We both know that much.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale received instruction from Elminster to go meet with Mystra at the Stormshore Tabernacle

Text.Value: Leave.
I suppose that's something.
Will you still love me when I'm a mind flayer?
Boyish charm and knees that creak like rusted hinges! Quite the combination.
Mr Dekarios, sir! Why - you're back!
I owe Mystra this. If I have a chance to earn her forgiveness, I have to take it.
I didn't say 'try'. I said 'promise'!
Excruciatingly awkward. On my side, at least.
Of course.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: You've got that quite the wrong way around, Mr Dekarios. She has lost you, and is a poorer goddess for it.
It's very unsettling how you can tell what I've been up to just by looking at me...
Leave.
Oh! Well! That's a better report than I feared.
I'm well past due to return to Waterdeep. I'm going to tell your mother that you'll be home soon. Don't make a liar of me, darling.
Naturally. After you abandoned her, there was only me left to keep her company.
Something like that. Don't worry - it's nothing I can't handle.
Attaboy! Keep doing what you're doing, then. We'll have this whole business sorted in no time.
Certainly not.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: Get to it, hmm?
But then whatever will we talk about?

EditorData.NodeContext: cheeky

Text.Value: The Absolute has to be stopped. I'm no great loss in the bargain.
Goodness. How awful that was.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: We are heading to Baldur's Gate, aren't we? You've always been very positive about the selection of books in Sorcerous Sundries. An opportunity for research, perhaps.
Mystra is a god, Gale. We pay her her due, but not with our lives. Your duty isn't to Mystra. Your duty is to return to Waterdeep. To continue your research, to live your life!
If you think that's bad, just wait 'til you find out what's in my head.
Hup hup, sir! Go on and have a read - I'd very much like to know this saga had a happy ending for my favourite fellow.
Nothing to report.
How long do you have?
So. What did Elminster have to say for himself?
Yes.
I bumped into Elminster. I say 'bumped into' - he was waiting for me outside Sorcerous Sundries.
Ah-ah. I will not be dismissed! Tell me, Gale. What's going on?
Away with you, then! I have no desire to bear witness to such a distasteful process.
How are things back in Waterdeep?
What's wrong with my beard?
Doing what, exactly? Last I checked, that orb is still pulsating inside you, vulgar as ever.
Finally a task worth completing. Do her this little favour, and she'll have no excuse not to cure that wretched orb of yours.
I'll be gone with the morning light, sir. Though one last fuss wouldn't go amiss before then.
You've been visiting my mother?
Indeed. It took me a good long while to find just the one - and an even longer while figuring out how to transport it here.
Oh. Interesting.
Oh yes, yes, yes - quite nice.
That's the spot, sir - thanking you.
Blessed Mystra, that's lovely.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Choices][Gale] bends down and scritches Tara behind the ears and/or above the tail [Tressym] enjoy it
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gale bends down and scritches TAra behind the ears and/or above the tail. She loves it. Purring sound effects.

Text.Value: I imagine that's going to be somewhat difficult to retrieve. But you're quite fond of accomplishing difficult feats, aren't you?
Scared you'd be hurt. Scared Mystra would punish you for your transgression. But do you know what never crossed my mind?
You're almost at the end of this, Gale. You're nearly there.
About time that old book-a-bones showed his face! I've been looking for him - for precisely the reason you outline.
You're going to kill me. And your mother. And then there'll be no one to mourn you when you've wasted yourself for no good reason at all.
LOUT!
I met with Mystra.
It went about as well as I expected.
He came with a message from Mystra. She wants to speak with me.
Mystra wants to see me, though I'm not sure I want to see her.
I'm honestly not sure. But don't worry - it's nothing I can't handle.
Who are you calling a pet?
I can't make that promise, Tara.
Surely there's another way. Use your head, Mr Dekarios. It's what you do best.
I never thought I'd have to convince you to prioritise a trip to a bookshop. Go on, then. Out with you!
You must choose, Gale. And you'll have to do it alone, I'm afraid.
I was... I was quite terrified you wouldn't return. What happened in there?
I'm afraid you won't like it very much...
Do go find out the gossip, won't you?
I discovered I can use the Crown of Karsus - currently atop the elder brain - to save myself.
You are to me. Or doesn't my opinion matter?

EditorData.NodeContext: She's dead sincere, but she's also a bit manipulative here.

Text.Value: You will tell me what she says, won't you? Of course you will.
Waterdeep has ten better bookshops on any given street.
And not a moment too soon. Myself, I must away to Waterdeep. Your mother will be worried silly not to have heard from either of us - and now I can bring her the good news.
A-slinking and a-stalking, of course. This is a fascinating area of the Realms - this cult of the Absolute is taking over like a bad rash.
Give Tara a good scritch.
I met our good friend Elminster. He stabilised the orb for me.
Gods! At this rate I'll have to give up the Weave and take up a crossbow. Get the gods out of our business entirely.
Leave.
I miss her too.
Control the orb? Control the brain?
You focus on that parasite. I daresay turning into a mind flayer may set that bomb off as quick as anything. No time to waste.
Don't let that stop you. There's a great deal I don't like, but I haven't keeled over yet.
No more pricey artefacts for you then, is that it? Excellent. You were quickly becoming the most expensive pet in the Realms.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a wink, she's being cheeky

Text.Value: As am I, Mr Dekarios.
A successful shopping trip, that's all.
I'll try.
Depends. Are mind flayers warm-blooded? If so, my prize napping spot on your lap won't be compromised. In which case, I suppose we could find an accord.
I'll tell her. With my Cat Flap of Displacement, I can afford the occasional visit. I'd bring you along, if I could. Perhaps some day.
Long enough to find a cure, I hope.
You will find a better solution to this whole 'Absolute' business, won't you? I'm always bragging about your ingenuity and I'd hate to be thought a liar.

EditorData.NodeContext: Strict, masking her concern - Gale's shown signs he won't blow himself up, so she's less mad at him

Text.Value: Give Tara a fuss.
Anyhow - I'm keeping my senses pricked for any sign of another item that might be of use to you. Hopefully something will turn up soon.
And if you can't find what you're looking for in Sorcerous Sundries, I'll go check them all. But for now - get on with it!
Leave.
Oh, I always knew Mystra had a good heart. Deep, deep down.
For now, I'm terribly glad you're all right. If I'd lost you to a giant brain, the irony would have been intolerable.
More or less the same - though news of some mad faction calling themselves 'Absolutists' is starting to trickle in.
Come now, don't keep me in suspense. How was your reunion with the Mother of All Magic?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale spoke with Mystra at the Stormshore Tabernacle, Tara knew of this quest.
EditorData.NodeContext: slightly wry
EditorData.logicalname: GALE MET MYSTRA, TARA KNEW ABOUT MEETING

Text.Value: If something's happened that I should know about, I'd rather you were honest with me. We are in this together, aren't we?
Whatever do you mean?
Karsus' powers should have perished with him. You cannot trust such powers. You know better than this, don't you?
Surely we have more important things to discuss, Tara.
What is it, Mr Dekarios? You look like you've seen a ghost.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale spoke with Mystra at the Stormshore Tabernacle, Tara knew of this quest.
EditorData.logicalname: GALE MET MYSTRA, TARA KNEW ABOUT MEETING

Text.Value: Then again... perhaps she's got something useful to say, for once.
Not another word out of you 'til you've consumed that artefact, Mr Dekarios.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Should be mad exclusive and flag checked false once the GotOneMagicItem flag is set on eating the item.

Text.Value: She just wanted to clear the air between us.
I'd never want to lose you, Tara. I'll return the Crown to Mystra.
Or maybe she'd just say something like, 'My Gale always was one to make the impossible possible.' Oh, but she adores you.

EditorData.NodeContext: With affection. Tara loves Gale's mom.

Text.Value: I think so.
She wants me to bring the Crown of Karsus to her when the elder brain is defeated. She said she can cure the orb.
Not on my life.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: Now Mr Dekarios - you know I'm as cynical about Mystra's recent behaviour as the next tressym, but if she's reached out to you like this, it must be important.
Please tell me you've at least made inroads when it comes to finding someone to settle down with. Myself and Mrs Dekarios are starting to think you intend to die alone.
Well then. No sense delaying a conversation like that. Who knows when she'll next demand you blow yourself up, after all?
Erm. Meow.
I need a moment, please.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: A cat?
Search carefully, sir. The good things are usually either behind glass, or buried under a stack of loathsome picture papers.
And why would you, after what she's asked of you?
Well, you know the gods. When they indulge in a bit of divine intervention, they do so like to pick their moments. Us mere mortals have no choice but to go along for the ride.

EditorData.NodeContext: begrudging

Text.Value: Oh. Well. That is... hm.
Always.

EditorData.NodeContext: Medium intensity - this is a 'backfill node' we want so we can use it to patch holes we might find in our dialogues at a later date if needed. Therefore, the context is very broad.

Text.Value: That sounds like a path well worth the walking! And I shall trot along right beside you. Or flutter. It really depends on the terrain.
She's very good company, though. Ah, the stories we've traded over toast and tea. You're a highly entertaining source of speculation.
She offered me a path to forgiveness. One I have a far better chance of surviving.
I told your mother not to worry. That if they were anything to worry about, Baldur's Gate would handle things quick-sharp. Keep them from spreading their tendrils north.
Just a gut feeling, I suppose. Nothing I can't handle.
DAYS?! Mystra preserve us.
There's a good humanoid. You had me scared for a moment here.
Chin up and keep at it, sir. And don't forget to pet your favourite tressym for good luck.
Don't worry. It's nothing I can't hande.
You get all your best ideas from books, don't you, sir? Your worst ones, too... but it's worth the risk.
Do hurry up and speak with Mystra, won't you? Curiosity might kill cats, but I assure you tardiness torments the tressym.
Ghastly boy. But fine. I'll take what I'm given and be grateful for it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated with Gale but can't force him to be more firm.

Text.Value: I can look after myself. And you, while I'm at it. But what's wrong, Gale? There's something on your mind. Out with it.
You're right. I should hear her out.
She told me the orb is actually the Karsite Weave. When I seize the Crown of Karsus, I'll be able to control it at last. I'll be a god.
The truth is a bit shocking. I was kidnapped by mind flayers, infected with a parasite, and left here after their ship crashed. Now I'm looking for a cure.
She wants me to bring the Crown of Karsus to her when the elder brain is defeated.
If anyone can beat this thing, it is you.
There's more to it than that, I'm afraid.
Leave.
About many things, actually. You left the tower in such a hurry, and you didn't leave an address.
Tell me, Tara. What have you been up to in my absence?
What's that? For a moment I thought my friend Mr Dekarios was near, but now I see it's only the ghost of one of Mystra's playthings.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara is angry at Gale, masking her hurt that he might die.

Text.Value: Nothing to concern yourself with. Just passing on an invitation from an old friend.
I can't risk putting her in danger.
I found the book I needed in Sorcerous Sundries. And I'm fairly positive Mystra knows about it.
We're heading to Baldur's Gate, aren't we? You've always been very positive about the selection of books in Sorcerous Sundries. An opportunity for research, perhaps.
Shoo then, Mr Dekarios. That crown isn't going to retrieve itself.
I was abducted on a nautiloid and infected with an illithid parasite.
I promise.
You'll do what she says, won't you?
I'll have to make up some good news for your dear mother, then. I'm going home, Gale. To look after Mrs Dekarios, and to remind you that there are people waiting for you in Waterdeep.
Oh, thank the heavens! The barbarous beard has been slain at last!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Greeting in the camp, before meeting Elminster.
EditorData.NodeContext: A shout of surprise. Talking about Gale's beard, which she detests

Text.Value: On second thoughts, never mind.
Much as I enjoy our little chats, Mr Dekarios, I think it's Elminster you must speak to.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Elminster 2 is currently in camp and needs to talk to Gale urgently

Text.Value: And, of course, your mother would still think you a prince, no matter how many tentacles you had. And with a nautiloid, you may even manage to visit her more often.
I'll consider what you've said. But I'm not making any promises.
Thank heavens! I thought I was going to have to claw some sense into you.
Tressyms are exceptionally intuitive. And also, you wear your emotions like a very garish cravat.
Promise me, Gale. Promise me you'll find another way. Promise me you'll return home, when this is all over.
Shoo, now! Off to see Elminster with you.
I bumped into Elminster. I say 'bumped into' - he was waiting for me outside Sorcerous Sundries.
How about a little love?
Consider this, Gale Dekarios: I forbid you to undertake this fool's errand.
But speculation only goes so far! Tell me, Mr Dekarios - how have you been?
And are you willing to speak with her?
I found the Heart of the Absolute. It was an elder brain, wearing a strange Netherese crown...
Rrriaow! AHEM! That is, you must tell me every detail, Mr Dekarios.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tara meows in excitement and anticiaption after hearing juicy gossip, and then startles, embarrassed that she let her feline instincts get the better of her.

Text.Value: Yes. Pleased to say I remain intact, with no signs of ceremorphosis or spontaneous combustion on the horizon.
So, what did Elminster have to say that he couldn't possibly have told me, your closest companion and confidante?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale spoke to Elminster 2 in camp and was given Mystra's instruction to come speak with her

Text.Value: That's just my boyish charm.

Synopsis: Main dialogue for Tara, Gale's Tressym, which allows him to discover his own backstory.
